<Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S2.T1.t1.r5.m2">b_{2n+2}\left(q\right)</Math>
</sentence>
  
<para xml:id="C28.S2.SS5.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="47" xml:id="C28.S2.SS5.p2.s1">
An equivalent formulation is given by <Math equation-number="28.2.21" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S2.E21">\begin{array}[]{ll}w^{\prime}_{\mbox{\tiny I}}(\tfrac{1}{2}\pi;a,q)=0,&amp;a=a_{2n }\left(q\right),\\ w_{\mbox{\tiny I}}(\tfrac{1}{2}\pi;a,q)=0,&amp;a=a_{2n+1}\left(q\right),\end{array}</Math> and <Math equation-number="28.2.22" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S2.E22">\begin{array}[]{ll}w^{\prime}_{\mbox{\tiny II}}(\tfrac{1}{2}\pi;a,q)=0,&amp;a=b_{2 n+1}\left(q\right),\\ w_{\mbox{\tiny II}}(\tfrac{1}{2}\pi;a,q)=0,&amp;a=b_{2n+2}\left(q\right),\end{array}</Math> where <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S2.SS5.p2.m1">n=0,1,2,\dots</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="48" xml:id="C28.S2.SS5.p2.s2">
When <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S2.SS5.p2.m2">q=0</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.2.23" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S2.E23">a_{n}\left(0\right)=n^{2}, if n=0,1,2,\dots,</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.2.24" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S2.E24">b_{n}\left(0\right)=n^{2}, if n=1,2,3,\dots</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="49" xml:id="C28.S2.SS5.p2.s3">
Near <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S2.SS5.p2.m3">q=0</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S2.SS5.p2.m4">a_{n}\left(q\right)</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S2.SS5.p2.m5">b_{n}\left(q\right)</Math> can be expanded in power series in <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S2.SS5.p2.m6">q</Math> (see §28.6(i)); elsewhere they are determined by analytic continuation (see §28.7).
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="50" xml:id="C28.S2.SS5.p2.s4">
For nonnegative real values of <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S2.SS5.p2.m7">q</Math> , see Figure 28.2.1.
</sentence>

</para>
          
<sentence sentence-num-in-section="51" xml:id="C28.S2.F1.s1">
