<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="78" xml:id="C28.S2.SS6.p2.s1">
When <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S2.SS6.p2.m1">q=0</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.2.29" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S2.E29">\mathrm{ce}_{0}\left(z,0\right)=1/\sqrt{2},\mathrm{ce}_{n}\left(z,0\right)=\cos\left(nz\right),\mathrm{se}_{n}\left(z,0\right)=\sin\left(nz\right), , if n=1,2,3,\dots</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C28.S2.SS6.p3">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="79" xml:id="C28.S2.SS6.p3.s1">
For simple roots <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S2.SS6.p3.m1">q</Math> of the corresponding equations (28.2.21) and (28.2.22), the functions are made unique by the normalizations <Math equation-number="28.2.30" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S2.E30">\int_{0}^{2\pi}\left(\mathrm{ce}_{n}\left(x,q\right)\right)^{2}\mathrm{d}x=\pi,\int_{0}^{2\pi}\left(\mathrm{se}_{n}\left(x,q\right)\right)^{2}\mathrm{d}x=\pi,</Math> the ambiguity of sign being resolved by (28.2.29) when <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S2.SS6.p3.m2">q=0</Math> and by continuity for the other values of <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S2.SS6.p3.m3">q</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C28.S2.SS6.p4">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="80" xml:id="C28.S2.SS6.p4.s1">
The functions are orthogonal, that is, <Math equation-number="28.2.31" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S2.E31">\int_{0}^{2\pi}\mathrm{ce}_{m}\left(x,q\right)\mathrm{ce}_{n}\left(x,q\right) \mathrm{d}x=0, if n\neq m,</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.2.32" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S2.E32">\int_{0}^{2\pi}\mathrm{se}_{m}\left(x,q\right)\mathrm{se}_{n}\left(x,q\right) \mathrm{d}x=0, if n\neq m,</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.2.33" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S2.E33">\int_{0}^{2\pi}\mathrm{ce}_{m}\left(x,q\right)\mathrm{se}_{n}\left(x,q\right) \mathrm{d}x=0</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C28.S2.SS6.p5">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="81" xml:id="C28.S2.SS6.p5.s1">
For change of sign of <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S2.SS6.p5.m1">q</Math> (compare (28.2.4))
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="82" xml:id="C28.S2.SS6.p5.s2">
<Math equation-number="28.2.34" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S2.E34">\mathrm{ce}_{2n}\left(z,-q\right)=(-1)^{n}\mathrm{ce}_{2n}\left(\tfrac{1}{2} \pi-z,q\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.2.35" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S2.E35">\mathrm{ce}_{2n+1}\left(z,-q\right)=(-1)^{n}\mathrm{se}_{2n+1}\left(\tfrac{1}{ 2}\pi-z,q\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.2.36" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S2.E36">\mathrm{se}_{2n+1}\left(z,-q\right)=(-1)^{n}\mathrm{ce}_{2n+1}\left(\tfrac{1}{ 2}\pi-z,q\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.2.37" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S2.E37">\mathrm{se}_{2n+2}\left(z,-q\right)=(-1)^{n}\mathrm{se}_{2n+2}\left(\tfrac{1}{ 2}\pi-z,q\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C28.S2.SS6.p6">

